ξ 9. SKETCH OF ROMAN HISTORY To 321 nc.

Rome, founded in 753 ss.c., was governed for two centuries and a half by kings. Within her walls men of Latin and of Sabine blood united to form a community less powerful at first than some of their neighbours. But, by the time that the king was replaced 509 13.c. by two annual consuls, Rome had won her way to some sort of headship of the Latin League.
